This paper deals with the application of sheaf theory to model the contextual nature of natural language and provide a global semantics for a discourse. This is a topic that falls under the subfield of computational linguistics (cs.CL). The paper also discusses the use of quantitative measures to rank multiple gluings, which is a topic that falls under the subfield of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also involves the use of mathematical structures to model language, which is a topic that falls under the subfield of theoretical computer science (cs.DS) and information theory (cs.IT).
